file=Engineering/dev/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: dev-logical-book-requirements\ntype: logical (placeholder — no book provided yet)\nstatus: awaiting source material; nothing here is a built logical skill until a real book/source is supplied\nassigned_agent: dev (Engineering / Lead Developer)\ndate_added: 2026-07-08\n · p:=Records what would ground dev's logical layer. None provided yet.\n · w:Dev Specifically Needs This=dev's judgments — "this architecture is sound," "this is acceptable debt," "boring beats novel here" — are principled but not formally grounded. Per rule 0.6 they are reasoning-based until sourced.\n · ca:Books (operator sources)=1. **A rigorous software-architecture text** (e.g., a recognized work on architecture trade-off analysis / fitness functions) — would give ADRs a citable method for weighing options and defining architectural fitness rather than judgment alone.\n2. **A site-reliability / production-operations text** (SRE-class) — grounds the design-for-failure and definition-of-done rules (error budgets, SLOs) with real method; shared domain with ops — coordinate, extract once.\n · wh:NOT to Use=Framework tutorials (stack-profile/dated-notes material), opinion-blog compilations without method.\n · i:for When a Book Is Provided=Standard: confirm edition/chapters → extract one framework at a time (rule 0.2) with citations → build as logical skills → cross-reference extension points (e.g., "fitness functions become an ADR field") → update `status`.\n · cs:Current Status=No book provided. No logical skills built.\n